## The Organism vs. The Machine

There is a deeper pattern here, one that connects this essay to everything that has come before.

The profit-maximising organisation is built on a *mechanical* metaphor. It sees itself as a machine: inputs, outputs, efficiency, optimisation. Parts can be replaced. Costs can be cut. The machine has no memory, no loyalty, no soul.

The purpose-driven organisation is built on an *organic* metaphor. It sees itself as a living system: interdependent, adaptive, growing. It has identity. It has memory. It has a reason to survive beyond the next quarter.

<Callout type="theological" title="The Edenic Connection">
